        ]
      },
      "transcript": {
        "text": {
          "en-AU": "Today we'll learn how to compare fractions! When fractions have the same denominator, we only need to compare the numerators. But when they have different denominators, we need to find a common way to compare them using visual models and equivalent fractions."
        }
      },
      "alt": "Instructional video for Compare Fractions",
      "ariaLabel": "Interactive video player: Compare Fractions"
    },
    {
      "kind": "guided_practice",
      "id": "guided_bH5nKx7z",
      "title": {
        "en-AU": "Practice: Compare Fractions"
      },
      "steps": [
        {
          "id": "step_1_mT9rQw8x",
          "instruction": {
            "en-AU": "Step 1"
          },
          "question": {
            "en-AU": "Which is larger: 2/4 or 1/4?"
          },
          "correctAnswer": "2/4",
          "hints": [
            {
              "en-AU": "When the bottom numbers are the same, compare the top numbers."
            },
            {
              "en-AU": "2 is greater than 1, so 2/4 is larger than 1/4."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "step_2_pL6kRy9n",
          "instruction": {
            "en-AU": "Step 2"
          },
          "question": {
            "en-AU": "Compare 1/2 and 1/3. Which is larger?"
          },
          "correctAnswer": "1/2",
          "hints": [
            {
              "en-AU": "When the top numbers are the same, the fraction with the smaller bottom number is larger."
            },
            {
              "en-AU": "Think of pizza slices: 1 out of 2 pieces is bigger than 1 out of 3 pieces."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "step_3_vK4mLx2q",
          "instruction": {
            "en-AU": "Step 3"
          },
          "question": {
            "en-AU": "Using the symbols <, >, or =, compare: 3/6 ___ 1/2"
          },
          "correctAnswer": "=",
          "hints": [
            {
              "en-AU": "First, check if these fractions are equivalent."
            },
            {
              "en-AU": "3/6 simplifies to 1/2, so they are equal."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
